# Runs on `git commit` BEFORE the commit is created.
#
# WHY lint-staged?
#   • Runs linters/formatters only on files in the staging area — fast even on huge repos.
#   • Auto-fixes (Prettier write, ESLint --fix) and re-stages, so the commit reflects
#     formatted code without an extra round-trip.
#
# If a check fails (e.g. ESLint error), the commit is aborted. Fix and re-stage.
# To skip in an emergency: `git commit --no-verify` (don't make a habit of it).
npx lint-staged
